  "text": "For Hoechst staining, cells were plated onto 96-well plates at a density of 1x10 6 cells/mL. For Western blot analysis and reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR), a cell density of 1x10 5 cells/ mL was used [CITATION_1] . In all studies, various concentrations (0, 0.1, 0.6, 1.2 and 6 μM) of Leu 5 AMD were added to Saos-2 cells and incubated for 0, 4, 8 and 24 h before subsequent analyses. Ethanol was used as a solvent control.",
